1
00:00:23,540 --> 00:00:28,450
♪Like a flock of birds
pressing ever forward♪

2
00:00:28,980 --> 00:00:33,350
♪Stranded on an island
shrouded in heavy mist♪

3
00:00:34,450 --> 00:00:38,410
♪We may seem small
beneath the vast world♪

4
00:00:38,410 --> 00:00:43,680
♪But not once have we felt despair♪

5
00:00:43,970 --> 00:00:46,770
♪We've crossed waves
a thousand layers deep♪

6
00:00:46,770 --> 00:00:49,530
♪Stepped on reefs hidden in the dark♪

7
00:00:49,530 --> 00:00:54,730
♪Facing sharper winds head-on♪

8
00:00:54,730 --> 00:00:57,660
♪Our wounds now stitched
into battle robes♪

9
00:00:57,660 --> 00:01:00,370
♪The long night
is branded by starlight♪

10
00:01:00,370 --> 00:01:05,440
♪We embrace this deep blue together♪

11
00:01:05,590 --> 00:01:10,620
♪At the edge of the vast unknown,
I remain unchanged♪

12
00:01:11,070 --> 00:01:16,540
♪Holding fast with lonely courage,
roaring without fear♪

13
00:01:16,670 --> 00:01:21,850
♪Determined to be
both my friend and my rival♪

14
00:01:22,140 --> 00:01:27,030
♪No one dares to blindly
urge me to turn back♪

15
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:32,090
♪I choose what I believe is worth it♪

16
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:38,340
=Rose and Gun=

17
00:01:38,940 --> 00:01:40,980
=Episode 18=

18
00:01:41,860 --> 00:01:42,660
Captain Wu.

19
00:01:43,940 --> 00:01:45,020
What should I do?

20
00:01:56,220 --> 00:01:57,500
Do you want this child?

21
00:01:57,660 --> 00:01:59,580
Yes, of course I do.

22
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:03,140
Do you know what having a child means?

23
00:02:15,980 --> 00:02:17,460
Do you know

24
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:19,380
what I remember most from my childhood?

25
00:02:21,380 --> 00:02:22,980
It was my mom waiting by the phone

26
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:25,820
every day, hoping it'd ring.

27
00:02:27,380 --> 00:02:28,700
Sometimes, we get

28
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:29,940
one phone call a week.

29
00:02:30,293 --> 00:02:31,780
Sometimes, we'll go one whole month,

30
00:02:31,780 --> 00:02:33,540
half a year, or even longer

31
00:02:33,660 --> 00:02:35,260
without a single call.

32
00:02:36,220 --> 00:02:37,540
You're not from a military family,

33
00:02:37,820 --> 00:02:38,940
so you don't understand.

34
00:02:39,460 --> 00:02:41,980
But it's pure suffering

35
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:44,900
for the kids and family.

36
00:02:47,460 --> 00:02:49,100
It's much better now.

37
00:02:49,780 --> 00:02:51,780
We can contact every week when off duty.

38
00:02:52,220 --> 00:02:53,380
When things are good,

39
00:02:53,980 --> 00:02:55,380
we can go home a few times a week.

40
00:02:58,380 --> 00:03:00,180
But that's not enough

41
00:03:00,540 --> 00:03:01,620
to raise a child.

42
00:03:02,621 --> 00:03:03,780
Even the basics,

43
00:03:04,980 --> 00:03:06,500
what if she can't eat from nausea?

44
00:03:07,048 --> 00:03:08,100
What if she can't walk

45
00:03:08,660 --> 00:03:10,260
and can't go to pregnancy checkups?

46
00:03:11,048 --> 00:03:12,940
What if you don't have leave
on her due date?

47
00:03:14,260 --> 00:03:16,060
You can't even be sure.

48
00:03:18,620 --> 00:03:20,460
Yangyang has to expect the worst.

49
00:03:20,460 --> 00:03:22,115
You should
see things from her perspective.

50
00:03:22,620 --> 00:03:24,540
She has to imagine
you'll be absent all the time.

51
00:03:24,540 --> 00:03:25,500
What should she do?

52
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:30,460
Captain Wu.

53
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:33,260
If it were you, what would you do?

54
00:03:36,620 --> 00:03:37,820
Just thinking

55
00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:40,540
of my pregnant wife

56
00:03:41,820 --> 00:03:42,980
getting up at night

57
00:03:43,780 --> 00:03:45,940
with no one there
to pour her a glass of water,

58
00:03:46,780 --> 00:03:48,460
makes my chest feel tight

59
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:49,100
and heavy.

60
00:03:50,340 --> 00:03:51,380
I understand you.

61
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:54,500
Yes, it's a huge responsibility.

62
00:03:55,220 --> 00:03:56,460
But you have to carry it.

63
00:03:57,100 --> 00:03:57,940
If you can't,

64
00:03:59,060 --> 00:04:00,700
everything you said at the warship

65
00:04:00,700 --> 00:04:01,820
was nonsense.

66
00:04:19,660 --> 00:04:20,340
Zong Qing.

67
00:04:20,660 --> 00:04:22,580
Explain the flag signals to the brides.

68
00:04:23,593 --> 00:04:24,820
Let the sea bear witness.

69
00:04:24,940 --> 00:04:26,260
With the ship as our matchmaker,

70
00:04:26,340 --> 00:04:27,580
we'll be together

71
00:04:27,780 --> 00:04:28,900
forever!

72
00:04:36,140 --> 00:04:37,500
What a rare guest.

73
00:04:37,871 --> 00:04:39,560
Sorry, I need to trouble you again.

74
00:04:39,582 --> 00:04:40,900
Something urgent came up at work.

75
00:04:40,900 --> 00:04:43,380
I'll leave Yangyang with you for a bit. I'll pick her up after.

76
00:04:43,460 --> 00:04:46,020
It's alright.
I just got off shift, so I'm free.

77
00:04:46,020 --> 00:04:48,460
Yangyang, you're with me today.

78
00:04:49,220 --> 00:04:50,940
Go on. Why are you being shy?

79
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:53,460
Mrs. Wang, sorry to trouble you.

80
00:04:54,061 --> 00:04:54,700
Bye.

81
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:55,340
Goodbye.

82
00:05:01,220 --> 00:05:02,020
Mrs. Wang.

83
00:05:02,140 --> 00:05:04,900
You're due soon.
Why are you still working?

84
00:05:05,220 --> 00:05:07,260
I still have a few days to go.

85
00:05:07,260 --> 00:05:09,220
Staying home is boring.

86
00:05:10,020 --> 00:05:11,460
Have you prepared everything?

87
00:05:11,460 --> 00:05:12,700
What's there to prepare?

88
00:05:12,700 --> 00:05:14,382
I'll just deliver the baby
when it's time.

89
00:05:16,460 --> 00:05:17,700
Want to touch her?

90
00:05:18,820 --> 00:05:19,500
No thanks.

91
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:20,700
Are you scared?

92
00:05:22,700 --> 00:05:24,220
Aren't you scared?

93
00:05:28,140 --> 00:05:29,820
What's there to fear?

94
00:05:29,820 --> 00:05:31,140
It's just pregnancy.

95
00:05:33,820 --> 00:05:36,100
When I was pregnant
with the first child,

96
00:05:36,380 --> 00:05:37,780
I was scared too.

97
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:40,500
Wang Lang was in the army then.

98
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:42,140
I stayed with my mother-in-law
back home.

99
00:05:42,820 --> 00:05:44,580
I watched my belly

100
00:05:44,780 --> 00:05:46,460
grow bigger day by day.

101
00:05:47,140 --> 00:05:48,940
I was so panicked.

102
00:05:49,273 --> 00:05:50,020
I thought

103
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:51,820
I was not even ready.

104
00:05:51,820 --> 00:05:53,460
How can I be a mom?

105
00:05:54,471 --> 00:05:57,340
The worst part was that Wang Lang
wasn't around during the pregnancy.

106
00:05:58,340 --> 00:05:59,580
Not until the due date

107
00:06:00,020 --> 00:06:01,780
did he get leave to come home.

108
00:06:01,820 --> 00:06:02,820
But who knew

109
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:05,500
he got an urgent order on the train.

110
00:06:05,820 --> 00:06:07,500
He was called back halfway.

111
00:06:08,260 --> 00:06:10,500
I broke down when I heard that.

112
00:06:10,820 --> 00:06:12,820
Wang Zhaoyang
was born prematurely that day.

113
00:06:14,620 --> 00:06:16,420
Three days after giving birth,

114
00:06:16,740 --> 00:06:18,860
Wang Lang finally called me.

115
00:06:19,620 --> 00:06:21,060
On the phone,

116
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:22,740
he was crying so much

117
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:25,260
that he couldn't even
finish apologizing.

118
00:06:26,180 --> 00:06:28,060
Brigadier cried?

119
00:06:29,380 --> 00:06:30,820
Have you heard a man cry?

120
00:06:31,860 --> 00:06:34,700
That kind where he chokes up

121
00:06:34,700 --> 00:06:36,060
and sounds terrible.

122
00:06:38,180 --> 00:06:40,180
It's like he's suffocating himself.

123
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:46,860
Actually, having a child
is a shared responsibility.

124
00:06:47,580 --> 00:06:48,940
But giving birth

125
00:06:49,060 --> 00:06:50,620
is something women face alone,

126
00:06:50,860 --> 00:06:53,060
from start to finish.

127
00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:55,620
You'll be pregnant for ten months.

128
00:06:55,620 --> 00:06:59,300
Think about it.
Not only does your body lose shape,

129
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:00,860
but your memory also worsens.

130
00:07:01,180 --> 00:07:03,620
You'll be throwing up every single day.

131
00:07:04,140 --> 00:07:05,740
In the end, your feet and hands

132
00:07:05,740 --> 00:07:08,020
will swell too much to wear shoes.

133
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:13,060
Especially during labor.

134
00:07:13,860 --> 00:07:15,020
The pain is so intense

135
00:07:16,380 --> 00:07:19,060
that you forget how to scream.

136
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:21,860
But it's strange.

137
00:07:22,740 --> 00:07:25,420
When the nurse

138
00:07:25,420 --> 00:07:26,740
places that ugly little thing

139
00:07:26,740 --> 00:07:28,380
on you,

140
00:07:31,180 --> 00:07:34,180
that wrinkly and red little hand

141
00:07:34,180 --> 00:07:36,060
just grabs your finger.

142
00:07:37,860 --> 00:07:39,260
In that moment,

143
00:07:39,820 --> 00:07:41,180
you instantly calm down

144
00:07:41,620 --> 00:07:43,180
and forget all about the pain.

145
00:07:43,580 --> 00:07:44,620
Your heart will melt.

146
00:07:48,060 --> 00:07:49,140
Mrs. Wang.

147
00:07:50,140 --> 00:07:51,380
I'm pregnant too.

148
00:07:51,860 --> 00:07:53,180
I could tell.

149
00:07:53,740 --> 00:07:56,260
That's why Xin brought you to me.

150
00:07:57,820 --> 00:08:00,060
But I don't know what to do.

151
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:01,620
I'm a little scared.

152
00:08:02,020 --> 00:08:02,880
Yangyang.

153
00:08:03,300 --> 00:08:04,300
Remember this.

154
00:08:04,620 --> 00:08:06,500
Giving birth is not a duty.

155
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:08,260
It's a personal choice.

156
00:08:08,860 --> 00:08:11,180
After I had Wang Zhaoyang,

157
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:12,180
I thought

158
00:08:12,180 --> 00:08:13,260
I'll never

159
00:08:13,260 --> 00:08:15,420
have a second child.

160
00:08:16,740 --> 00:08:18,020
But look at me now.

161
00:08:19,420 --> 00:08:20,820
Pregnancy is tough.

162
00:08:21,260 --> 00:08:22,580
But you know what?

163
00:08:23,060 --> 00:08:25,060
After the baby is born,

164
00:08:25,060 --> 00:08:26,620
many unexpected things

165
00:08:26,620 --> 00:08:28,180
will happen.

166
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:29,140
Really.

167
00:08:29,620 --> 00:08:30,580
So

168
00:08:30,860 --> 00:08:32,380
I hope you think it through.

169
00:08:40,420 --> 00:08:41,500
(I forgot to tell you.)

170
00:08:41,850 --> 00:08:44,020
(The day after you gave
the porcelain shards to Wu Si,)

171
00:08:44,020 --> 00:08:45,680
(I sent them to the museum.)

172
00:08:45,871 --> 00:08:48,220
(I hope it would catch
Cultural Relics Bureau's attention.)

173
00:08:48,220 --> 00:08:48,860
(Also,)

174
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:52,740
(if it's true that someone is stealing
underwater cultural relics)

175
00:08:53,380 --> 00:08:55,260
(more relics)

176
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:57,140
(will be smuggled overseas)

177
00:08:57,300 --> 00:08:58,800
(for every day we delay.)

178
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:09,380
Xin, Mr. Tian asked you
to join the meeting.

179
00:09:09,460 --> 00:09:10,260
Got it.

180
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:15,460
(Atocha,)

181
00:09:15,780 --> 00:09:17,540
(a company registered
in the Roman Islands.)

182
00:09:18,020 --> 00:09:19,620
(Check out that company.)

183
00:09:19,860 --> 00:09:22,100
(The address is 56, Torini Street.)

184
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:24,860
(What can I find with just a name)

185
00:09:25,140 --> 00:09:26,260
(and an address?)

186
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:29,660
(Then it's up to your abilities.)

187
00:09:33,340 --> 00:09:34,780
(I'm just a reporter.)

188
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:36,460
(I'm not that powerful.)

189
00:09:36,660 --> 00:09:38,020
(Any other leads?)

190
00:09:38,020 --> 00:09:39,540
(Tell me all of them.)

191
00:09:42,910 --> 00:09:44,460
(That's all for now.)

192
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:55,820
(One New Email Received)

193
00:09:56,340 --> 00:09:58,620
(But perhaps you'll get lucky)

194
00:09:58,620 --> 00:10:00,260
(and find something.)

195
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:06,093
Find me a company

196
00:10:06,093 --> 00:10:07,540
registered in the Roman Islands.

197
00:10:07,740 --> 00:10:08,860
Is it related to the relics?

198
00:10:08,982 --> 00:10:10,860
It's important.
I need all the information.

199
00:10:14,020 --> 00:10:14,780
Mrs. Wang.

200
00:10:15,340 --> 00:10:17,260
I don't feel anything.

201
00:10:17,660 --> 00:10:19,260
I'm not happy

202
00:10:19,540 --> 00:10:20,860
or excited at all.

203
00:10:21,020 --> 00:10:22,260
I don't look forward to it.

204
00:10:22,900 --> 00:10:24,660
Am I unfit to be a mom?

205
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:26,540
Of course not.

206
00:10:27,540 --> 00:10:28,380
Do you know

207
00:10:28,380 --> 00:10:29,740
when I stopped regretting?

208
00:10:31,540 --> 00:10:33,340
When Wang Zhaoyang turned one month old.

209
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:36,140
Wang Lang applied for leave
and came home.

210
00:10:36,660 --> 00:10:38,020
I recall waking up

211
00:10:38,740 --> 00:10:39,780
one morning

212
00:10:39,780 --> 00:10:42,020
to vaguely see Wang Lang

213
00:10:43,260 --> 00:10:45,860
clumsily feeding the baby.

214
00:10:46,140 --> 00:10:47,460
Scared to wake me,

215
00:10:47,471 --> 00:10:48,620
he didn't turn on the light.

216
00:10:48,660 --> 00:10:50,020
He just opened

217
00:10:50,020 --> 00:10:51,660
a small slit between the curtains,

218
00:10:52,140 --> 00:10:54,140
turned the baby toward it,

219
00:10:54,260 --> 00:10:56,140
and tried to feed the baby the pacifier.

220
00:10:56,900 --> 00:10:59,460
He was so clumsy
that he was sweating all over.

221
00:11:01,380 --> 00:11:03,020
Watching him like that...

222
00:11:04,660 --> 00:11:05,540
Honestly,

223
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:08,500
when Wang Zhaoyang misbehaves

224
00:11:08,620 --> 00:11:10,380
or Wang Lang upsets me,

225
00:11:10,380 --> 00:11:11,780
I think of that day.

226
00:11:13,020 --> 00:11:14,540
I think

227
00:11:15,260 --> 00:11:16,660
of the warm sunlight

228
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:18,893
that shone through the slit that day.

229
00:11:22,260 --> 00:11:23,140
And I'll feel

230
00:11:23,780 --> 00:11:24,860
that

231
00:11:25,226 --> 00:11:26,140
it's all worth it.

232
00:11:31,140 --> 00:11:32,260
Can I touch her?

233
00:11:32,260 --> 00:11:33,380
Of course.

234
00:11:38,620 --> 00:11:39,860
She's turning around

235
00:11:40,140 --> 00:11:41,260
to say hi to you.

236
00:11:41,260 --> 00:11:42,260
Did you feel it?

237
00:11:44,140 --> 00:11:45,900
Our little one is saying

238
00:11:46,340 --> 00:11:48,020
"Yangyang,

239
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:51,260
we'll be meeting very soon."

240
00:12:05,020 --> 00:12:05,740
How did it go?

241
00:12:07,380 --> 00:12:08,540
I did find something.

242
00:12:08,540 --> 00:12:09,380
This company

243
00:12:09,380 --> 00:12:11,500
(Atocha, 56, Torini Street)
is registered in the Roman Islands,

244
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:12,860
but I couldn't find anything else.

245
00:12:12,900 --> 00:12:15,380
Maybe try pressing
your informant again.

246
00:12:15,380 --> 00:12:16,740
If he relents,

247
00:12:17,260 --> 00:12:18,780
he might tell you others.

248
00:12:18,860 --> 00:12:20,380
I've pressed him for days

249
00:12:20,380 --> 00:12:22,260
before he told me about Atocha.

250
00:12:24,620 --> 00:12:26,140
Alright, work on something else.

251
00:12:26,140 --> 00:12:27,271
I'll think of something.

252
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:31,660
Dad, Mom, I'm home.

253
00:12:33,140 --> 00:12:33,860
You're home.

254
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:35,780
Hurry over.

255
00:12:36,540 --> 00:12:37,660
Let me officially

256
00:12:37,660 --> 00:12:39,500
announce some good news.

257
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:41,380
What good news?

258
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:43,140
Lan Yangyang

259
00:12:44,740 --> 00:12:45,740
is pregnant.

260
00:12:47,140 --> 00:12:49,140
This is great news.

261
00:12:50,020 --> 00:12:51,660
I'll call Lan Weiguo later

262
00:12:51,660 --> 00:12:52,660
to congratulate him.

263
00:12:53,260 --> 00:12:54,660
At the very least, Xin should share

264
00:12:54,660 --> 00:12:56,500
some good fortune
from his becoming a grandpa.

265
00:12:57,380 --> 00:12:59,140
Dad, must you always

266
00:12:59,140 --> 00:13:00,620
drag me into everything?

267
00:13:00,620 --> 00:13:02,260
Who else would I drag in?

268
00:13:02,860 --> 00:13:03,860
I'm just jealous.

269
00:13:05,020 --> 00:13:06,020
Look at them.

270
00:13:07,380 --> 00:13:08,740
How annoying.

271
00:13:11,020 --> 00:13:11,737
Let me help you.

272
00:13:12,140 --> 00:13:13,140
How nice.

273
00:13:26,260 --> 00:13:27,100
Sergeant Cheng.

274
00:13:27,980 --> 00:13:29,260
What's up with Captain Zong?

275
00:13:29,260 --> 00:13:30,740
How long will he run for?

276
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:33,140
You don't get it.

277
00:13:33,860 --> 00:13:36,620
He'll stop running
when he figures things out.

278
00:13:43,620 --> 00:13:45,493
Captain Zong, your wife texted you.

279
00:13:45,493 --> 00:13:47,715
Are you going to read it?
If not, I'll toss your phone.

280
00:13:57,560 --> 00:14:00,540
(Lan Yangyang:
I'm going to Dad's. Talk later.)

281
00:14:07,140 --> 00:14:07,740
What?

282
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:14,140
No, again?

283
00:14:25,260 --> 00:14:26,500
What happened?

